01:26.434 --> 01:28.177
- Thanks a lot, man.
- You bet.

01:28.269 --> 01:30.095
- Cool. Take care.
- You, too.

01:34.024 --> 01:36.147
Harp, how's it goin', brother?

01:43.782 --> 01:47.364
Robin, baby, I got some good news.

01:47.452 --> 01:51.034
- Try this. Tell me what you think.
- Come on, girl. You know...

01:51.164 --> 01:55.540
Grilled ginger shrimp
with cranberry-orange-mango chutney.

01:55.627 --> 01:59.291
- Damn, that's good.
- Yeah, man, 'tis good.

02:04.175 --> 02:08.753
Thanks for letting me use your kitchen.
I almost died when my stove broke.

02:08.971 --> 02:10.631
No problem, baby.

02:10.847 --> 02:14.050
But then I remembered
what a loving boyfriend I have.

02:18.271 --> 02:19.848
Sorry about the mess.

02:20.106 --> 02:23.805
I have three jobs goin' on at once here.

02:24.359 --> 02:26.767
- It's so crazy.
- So I see.

02:26.863 --> 02:28.771
What's the news?

02:28.863 --> 02:30.488
What's the dealie, yo?

02:33.201 --> 02:36.949
Oprah Winfrey wants my new book,
Unfinished Business...

02:37.371 --> 02:40.455
for her January
Book of the Month Club Show.

02:40.790 --> 02:42.996
- You're kidding.
- I ain't kiddin'.

02:43.126 --> 02:45.794
Oh, my God! Your first novel?

02:46.170 --> 02:49.669
I was nervous when I heard
she wanted to read a preview copy.

02:49.798 --> 02:51.837
But she read it and loved it.

02:52.301 --> 02:55.586
- When's the release date?
- We go into print next month.

02:55.678 --> 02:59.759
Oh, baby! I'm so happy for you.

03:01.434 --> 03:04.054
I'm so happy for you!

03:05.353 --> 03:07.512
That is so great. So great.

03:07.606 --> 03:09.563
- I'm on my way, girl.
- The callaloo.

03:19.992 --> 03:21.651
I missed you.

03:23.620 --> 03:27.533
I'm glad you decided to come back
to town before heading to New York.

03:28.582 --> 03:31.536
Yeah. Me, too, baby.

03:33.336 --> 03:36.503
Did I tell you about the
20-city book tour I got going?

03:37.048 --> 03:41.875
I'm psyched. I gotta make sure
my shit's on point, though.

03:42.469 --> 03:46.169
- Harper, come on.
- "Harper, come on," what?

03:46.891 --> 03:48.965
You never live enough for today.

03:49.099 --> 03:51.935
For once, just enjoy the moment.

03:52.103 --> 03:53.727
At least for a little while?

03:53.812 --> 03:55.604
I got to stay focused.

03:55.731 --> 03:58.815
All work and no play
makes Harper a very dull boy.

03:58.900 --> 04:02.234
- Yeah, whatever, man.
- "Yeah, whatever, man."

04:03.363 --> 04:05.271
You're not feelin' me, huh?

04:06.615 --> 04:10.447
I felt you getting your freak on a
couple minutes ago. That's what I felt.

04:10.535 --> 04:13.370
- Only with you.
- That's what I like to hear.

04:16.248 --> 04:17.624
Oh, girl.

04:19.834 --> 04:22.540
I could be like this
with you forever, Harper.

04:24.214 --> 04:25.209
What?

04:26.299 --> 04:27.497
Relax.

04:30.053 --> 04:33.137
All I mean is that I
love being with you.

04:34.849 --> 04:38.217
You said yourself I was the
best girlfriend you ever had.

04:38.310 --> 04:41.678
You've never been with somebody
this long or had this much fun.

04:41.771 --> 04:43.894
Face it. We fit together.

04:45.817 --> 04:48.057
- Yeah, but...
- You love me, don't you?

04:48.610 --> 04:51.647
Of course I do. But
it's not that simple.

04:52.822 --> 04:54.613
It is to me.

05:06.501 --> 05:07.698
Dead silence.

05:08.837 --> 05:10.246
Nice. Excuse me.

05:11.130 --> 05:13.121
What's "Excuse me"? Wait.

05:13.257 --> 05:16.043
No. I think I'll get some sleep.

05:16.135 --> 05:17.415
Wait, Robin.

05:33.734 --> 05:36.402
Honey, about last night. I didn't...

05:36.986 --> 05:40.437
Harper, it's okay. I know you love me.

05:40.530 --> 05:43.365
- I do, you know.
- I'm not insecure.

05:44.952 --> 05:47.524
- I just have doubts sometimes.
- About what?

05:47.619 --> 05:50.241
Like this wedding reunion
with your friends.

05:51.498 --> 05:53.289
I don't know what I'm walking into.

05:53.375 --> 05:56.494
Oh, baby! They are gonna love you.

05:56.586 --> 05:59.255
Don't worry. They are gonna love you.
You'll be fine.

05:59.339 --> 06:00.501
- Really?
- Really.

06:00.590 --> 06:02.000
Even Kendall?

06:07.428 --> 06:11.426
I can't believe you're jealous of
a character I wrote in my book.

06:11.683 --> 06:14.352
Not just a character. An icon. An ideal.

06:14.435 --> 06:17.388
Your soul mate. Jackson's soul mate.

06:20.399 --> 06:23.316
- She's nothing like me.
- She's not like anybody.

06:24.193 --> 06:28.107
She is a combination of a bunch of women
that I knew in college.

06:28.238 --> 06:32.402
- Why would I lie to you about that?
- I don't know. That's what scares me.

06:33.452 --> 06:37.234
Okay, here it is. Here is the drama.

06:37.330 --> 06:40.995
I thought I had finally avoided it
in this relationship.

06:41.084 --> 06:43.041
I'm not perfect.

06:43.042 --> 06:44.997
Could we stop talking
about this, please?

06:46.880 --> 06:48.671
I had to let you know how I feel.

06:48.757 --> 06:51.877
- Are you still coming to the wedding?
- Of course I am.

06:52.093 --> 06:54.334
Nothing has changed about that.

06:55.638 --> 06:57.796
I want you to have fun.

06:58.223 --> 07:00.548
Hang out with your boys, reminisce.

07:02.394 --> 07:04.386
I'll still be there on Sunday.

07:04.645 --> 07:06.603
That's great. Fine. Good.

07:11.902 --> 07:15.817
Atlantic Airlines welcomes you
to New York City's La Guardia Airport.

07:17.115 --> 07:18.442
I'm coming!

07:34.337 --> 07:35.582
Harper!

07:37.340 --> 07:39.083
Murch! My man!

07:39.217 --> 07:41.375
It's the Doug Banks Show
with DeDe McGuire.

07:41.470 --> 07:44.885
Can you believe those Giants?
Lance Sullivan, my man!

07:44.973 --> 07:48.222
That man really is. He's fine.
Big old chocolate thing.

07:48.308 --> 07:51.559
- No, DeDe, he's a good football player.
- I know. I'm a fan.

07:51.645 --> 07:53.601
Right. Here's Lauryn Hill.

07:53.688 --> 07:55.728
What do you say about that?
So, they're fine.

07:55.729 --> 07:57.767
They're young, that's all.

07:57.859 --> 08:01.393
And I had to take a gun away
from one kid last week.

08:02.071 --> 08:03.695
Hell, no! A gun?

08:05.240 --> 08:06.782
Damn it, Murch!

08:06.866 --> 08:10.400
Didn't the firm you worked for last
summer offer you a six-figure salary?

08:10.494 --> 08:12.866
- Yes, they did.
- So what's up?

08:12.955 --> 08:14.912
I have to pass the bar first.

08:15.124 --> 08:16.535
Whatever, man.

08:17.333 --> 08:20.703
Brother, all I'm saying is,
if you're gonna be stressed...

08:21.087 --> 08:22.795
get paid for it, man.

08:23.840 --> 08:25.631
Now you sound like Shelby.

08:26.634 --> 08:27.832
Shelby.

08:28.510 --> 08:29.673
Lockdown!

08:32.514 --> 08:35.679
You are lucky I love you
like an adopted brother.

08:36.642 --> 08:38.801
I'm playing. Shelby's cool.

08:40.104 --> 08:43.222
You certainly didn't make her sound cool
in your book.

08:44.899 --> 08:47.355
I mean, not that I read your book.

08:47.485 --> 08:49.063
- You read my book?
- No.

08:50.112 --> 08:54.192
- How did you get ahold of my book?
- I don't have your book. Jordan does.

08:54.324 --> 08:55.902
Jordan has my book?

08:56.952 --> 08:58.695
Camera two,
I need a close-up on Dr. Gayle.

08:59.162 --> 09:01.320
Zoom in slowly, slowly.

09:01.956 --> 09:03.783
Great. Hold it right there.

09:03.874 --> 09:06.412
Camera one, stand by
for audience reaction.

09:06.501 --> 09:08.874
Give me audience reaction, camera one.

09:12.674 --> 09:14.049
Jordan Armstrong.

09:14.926 --> 09:17.417
She's already runnin' things, ain't she?

09:17.636 --> 09:19.546
You should not be surprised.

09:19.847 --> 09:22.469
She's the only one more driven
than you are.

09:23.100 --> 09:24.380
That's all right.

09:24.476 --> 09:29.268
- When's the last time you saw Jordan?
- Last March, actually.

09:29.814 --> 09:32.731
We didn't have much time to hang
'cause she had a deadline.

09:32.816 --> 09:34.774
And I had to move...

09:38.447 --> 09:39.609
What, nigger?

09:39.739 --> 09:42.942
You, my brother,
are withholding information.

09:43.117 --> 09:44.527
Here we go.

09:44.661 --> 09:47.115
You and Jordan got busy
in undergrad, didn't you?

09:47.204 --> 09:48.614
No, we didn't.

09:48.914 --> 09:52.116
What about the book?
Jackson and Kendall.

09:52.376 --> 09:53.917
That's you two. I know it!

09:54.002 --> 09:57.452
They picked the prime opportunity
to make grass sandwiches.

09:59.047 --> 10:01.373
"A passionate night
of lovemaking so intense..."

10:01.466 --> 10:04.218
I know my words.
Embellishment sells books.

10:05.386 --> 10:07.462
So, then what really happened?

10:09.431 --> 10:13.381
- Nothin'.
- You are lying! I know it.

10:13.853 --> 10:15.347
- Out with it.
- What?

10:15.520 --> 10:17.512
- Tell me. Tell me.
- Nothing.

10:23.277 --> 10:25.685
It was senior year during finals.

10:26.571 --> 10:28.677
The year-end issue was
off to the printer

10:28.678 --> 10:30.783
and the staff had left for the night.

10:30.868 --> 10:34.567
We both had studying to do,
but we were mad tired.

10:35.704 --> 10:38.540
Only Stevie Wonder
was gonna help us that night.

12:11.955 --> 12:15.537
- And you didn't tell any of us?
- There wasn't much to tell.

12:15.624 --> 12:17.701
And you know, you can't keep a secret.

12:17.794 --> 12:20.462
What do you mean I can't keep a secret?

12:20.796 --> 12:23.713
Were you supposed to tell me
that you had my book?

12:26.635 --> 12:28.010
Just finish the story.

12:58.788 --> 13:03.284
In retrospect, it was one of those
moments you wish you could have back.

13:04.626 --> 13:07.745
- But at the time, it just wasn't right.
- Wasn't right?

13:07.962 --> 13:10.121
- No.
- You two are ridiculous.

13:10.215 --> 13:11.127
Why?

13:11.214 --> 13:14.714
You forget. She was off to LA
to do that internship...

13:14.802 --> 13:16.794
I was headed straight to grad school.

13:16.887 --> 13:21.429
In other words, the two control freaks
couldn't lose control and get freaky?

13:24.434 --> 13:27.435
I almost forgot how corny you could be.

13:27.813 --> 13:29.141
Almost.

13:29.231 --> 13:32.765
- I thought it was a good play on words.
- It was kind of corny.

13:32.984 --> 13:34.016
Okay.

13:37.112 --> 13:38.940
Jordan, stop it.

13:39.031 --> 13:41.155
This is business.

13:41.825 --> 13:44.150
This is your boy. This
is strictly business.

13:44.244 --> 13:46.651
- It's all good. You don't have...
- Good job.

13:46.746 --> 13:49.416
Thanks, Anita. I think it was good,
but we could've...

13:49.499 --> 13:50.697
Is that him?

13:51.751 --> 13:55.450
Yes, indeed. That is Harper Stewart,
Lance Sullivan's best man.

13:55.713 --> 13:59.211
You sure we can't get a camera
at that wedding? It could be huge.

13:59.299 --> 14:02.583
I know. I've been working on that,
but they're adamant about it.

14:02.677 --> 14:03.840
Keep trying.

14:06.471 --> 14:07.551
Right.

14:07.847 --> 14:09.129
You ready?

14:12.936 --> 14:14.098
Ready.

14:18.024 --> 14:21.606
- Here she is.
- Harper Stewart.

14:22.235 --> 14:23.647
Jordan Armstrong.

14:24.238 --> 14:29.029
I've always enjoyed your writing.
But that book of yours? You nailed it.

14:29.200 --> 14:30.991
And your girl here. Talk about a fan.

14:31.076 --> 14:33.946
She's got her nose
in that preview copy every moment.

14:34.121 --> 14:36.872
It's my job to keep up
with what's current.

14:36.956 --> 14:38.498
Of course you do.

14:38.958 --> 14:42.790
Can we get you on Teen Summit,
or profile you on Tonight With Tavis?

14:43.713 --> 14:46.915
- Absolutely. Sure. I would like that.
- Great.

14:47.174 --> 14:49.499
We'll get Jordan to produce it.
What do you think?

14:49.593 --> 14:52.084
Absolutely. We've got the inside track.

14:53.554 --> 14:56.970
This is gonna be fabulous.
It was a pleasure meeting you both.

14:57.057 --> 15:00.427
- I've got to run. Take care, Harper.
- All right. Bye-bye.

15:02.646 --> 15:04.768
That's gonna be Jordan
in a little while.

15:04.855 --> 15:07.429
- She's well on her way.
- True.

15:08.151 --> 15:10.059
Come on, now. Give me love.

15:10.694 --> 15:12.237
Yeah, of course.

15:14.239 --> 15:17.655
Okay. Yeah. So, you know...

15:19.076 --> 15:22.445
Like Anita was saying,
we want to get you in the studio.

15:22.954 --> 15:25.955
You know me. I'm all yours.

15:30.586 --> 15:31.831
Right.

15:32.797 --> 15:35.962
Yeah. So, you guys ready to go?

15:36.425 --> 15:40.636
I'll talk to you later. 'Bye.
Damn, this wedding shit! It never ends.

15:40.721 --> 15:42.759
- Who wants ham hocks?
- Lance's uncles.

15:42.847 --> 15:46.133
Mia's cousins have the nerve
to be calling me, driving me nuts...

15:46.225 --> 15:48.384
asking me to hook them up with guys.

15:48.478 --> 15:51.929
- You should introduce them to Quentin.
- I did. Big mistake.

15:52.230 --> 15:54.353
He's got the poor girls open.

15:54.441 --> 15:57.358
- Charming motherfucker.
- That's what he's good at.

15:57.944 --> 16:01.526
If they gave college credit for that,
he'd have his Ph.D. By now.

16:03.657 --> 16:05.982
You know, Dr. Feelgood has your book.

16:06.494 --> 16:08.700
Quentin has my book?

16:36.978 --> 16:39.266
- Go on, baby.
- Quentin Spivey!

17:05.752 --> 17:08.375
Quentin Spivey from
our nation's capital.

17:10.423 --> 17:13.045
I'm gonna have to do a story on him.

17:13.175 --> 17:15.666
- I'll be right back.
- All right, cool.

17:16.054 --> 17:17.678
- You want a drink?
- No.

17:18.137 --> 17:20.712
- What's wrong with you?
- You talk too much.

17:20.848 --> 17:23.554
- See you later. Peace.
- Why'd you tell him everything?

17:24.770 --> 17:27.686
So, Q, what's up with the guitar?

17:29.023 --> 17:33.436
This? Just a little something
to add to the repertoire.

17:34.195 --> 17:37.693
- You know a nigger got gifts.
- The nigger's scatterbrained.

17:38.073 --> 17:41.406
I had to pull strings to get you
that photography gig at the Post.

17:41.492 --> 17:44.529
- What happened?
- Don't get all bent.

17:46.288 --> 17:47.782
You know I read your book.

17:47.873 --> 17:50.328
I heard. So?

17:50.667 --> 17:53.751
So, you got skills, Joe.

17:54.837 --> 17:58.088
I ain't gonna front.
You about to blow the fuck up.

17:58.716 --> 18:00.905
Get me wanting to
be a writer and shit.

18:00.906 --> 18:03.093
See, man, that's what
I'm talkin' about.

18:03.386 --> 18:06.969
First it was photography.
Then you got this music thing going.

18:07.056 --> 18:11.005
Back in January,
you wanted to direct music videos.

18:11.311 --> 18:15.141
- Now you want to be a writer.
- Don't sweat none of that shit, Joe.

18:16.147 --> 18:19.481
Seriously, that book is like that.

18:20.068 --> 18:23.899
I still think you might have exaggerated
a brother's character a little bit.

18:23.988 --> 18:27.819
My Mama not being around ain't got shit
to do with how I treat these bitches.

18:27.908 --> 18:29.817
How do you know I'm talkin' about you?

18:29.909 --> 18:32.826
Come on, now.
Give a nigger some credit, all right?

18:33.621 --> 18:37.950
I ain't stupid. I was more focused
than that when I was in school.

18:38.042 --> 18:39.785
You're still in school.

18:39.919 --> 18:41.875
But I'm sayin'...

18:42.421 --> 18:45.456
couldn't you have embellished
a nigger a little bit?

18:45.548 --> 18:48.465
Ain't that that buttery shit
about being a writer?

18:48.676 --> 18:51.132
You know, rewritin' history?

18:53.638 --> 18:56.757
Tailorin' shit to fit
your own ideal self?

18:56.976 --> 19:00.593
I know where you're going,
so just chill with that.

19:00.811 --> 19:02.769
The frontal lobe, shorty?

19:03.063 --> 19:07.227
- Ain't nothin' there. Just leave it be.
- All I'm sayin' is...

19:07.818 --> 19:10.189
it brought back some wild memories.

19:10.403 --> 19:13.155
You know, shit I ain't thought about
in years.

19:13.281 --> 19:14.989
Know what I'm sayin'?

19:17.451 --> 19:19.610
Yeah, man. Where's the book now?

19:26.459 --> 19:27.835
Running back!

19:51.273 --> 19:54.475
- You know what? You play too much.
- You're spilling your stuff.

19:54.566 --> 19:56.725
- That was a great show.
- Thank you.

19:56.986 --> 19:58.610
Can you imagine? Look at him.

19:58.696 --> 20:00.106
L-Boogie!

20:00.196 --> 20:03.695
- They love him in the Big Apple.
- You know they're talkin' Super Bowl.

20:03.783 --> 20:05.443
What are they now? 6 and 0?

20:05.534 --> 20:08.570
He's been carryin' them
all the way to the bye week.

20:10.289 --> 20:13.326
We gotta move back here.
I got you all set up back here.

20:16.294 --> 20:18.750
- I'm gonna go get the superstar.
- What you up to?

20:18.838 --> 20:21.673
- I'm not up to anything.
- Still got your mama's jacket on.

20:21.757 --> 20:23.583
Will you stop, you two?

20:24.551 --> 20:27.255
- Excuse me. Mr. Lance Sullivan?
- Thank you.

20:28.596 --> 20:30.885
- Harper, man! What's up?
- How you feelin'?

20:30.974 --> 20:34.508
- I'm all right, but I am stressed.
- You ought to be.

20:34.602 --> 20:37.685
Why are you planning a wedding
in the middle of the season?

20:37.771 --> 20:40.476
- You got Dallas next week.
- I wasn't even thinking.

20:40.565 --> 20:42.356
It's what the little lady wanted.

20:42.442 --> 20:45.015
The best man is here.
I'm gonna hook you up.

20:45.111 --> 20:47.317
I'll get you over that
broom if it kills me.

20:47.405 --> 20:49.065
Good to see you, man.

20:50.032 --> 20:51.231
How are you?

20:51.658 --> 20:55.702
- Sorry I missed your show.
- Congratulations, big man.

20:56.913 --> 20:58.952
- You doing all right?
- Yes, sir.

20:59.165 --> 21:00.873
- Congratulations.
- Thanks.

21:00.958 --> 21:01.989
Julian!

21:04.461 --> 21:06.537
Hi, Shel.

21:07.756 --> 21:09.380
Hello, honey.

21:12.009 --> 21:15.591
Well, well, well.
The gang's all here, back in effect.

21:16.137 --> 21:19.589
- Break out the forties.
- Hey, Shelby.

21:20.600 --> 21:22.676
It's nice to see all of you, too.

21:25.814 --> 21:27.306
Harper Stewart.

21:28.107 --> 21:32.353
- Richard Wrong, Langston Snooze.
- Hi, Shelby.

21:32.486 --> 21:35.901
I heard about your book,
and I don't think it's cute.

21:36.364 --> 21:40.860
Next time you want to characterize me
in one of your projects, do me a favor.

21:41.243 --> 21:43.366
- What would that be?
- Don't.

21:44.788 --> 21:48.287
Drive me to Saks. I can't decide
what I should wear for the wedding.

21:48.374 --> 21:51.957
- I thought you were wearing...
- No, no. I decided against that.

21:55.047 --> 21:57.419
I thought I told you I had plans.

21:57.842 --> 21:59.880
What kind of plans?

21:59.967 --> 22:03.466
- I'm hanging out with the guys tonight.
- Honey, that can wait.

22:03.554 --> 22:07.551
You have all weekend for that.
This'll only take a few hours. Come on.

22:16.607 --> 22:17.770
I see.

22:18.734 --> 22:20.726
It's "Gang up on Shelby" day.

22:21.528 --> 22:22.607
Fine.

22:22.905 --> 22:25.822
If you'd rather be with them than me,
that's fine.

22:26.783 --> 22:28.277
Here it comes.

22:30.995 --> 22:32.952
Am I being that unreasonable?

22:35.875 --> 22:37.155
No.

22:37.334 --> 22:40.085
Honey, no. No, no. I'm sorry.

22:40.545 --> 22:42.501
Murch, we'll catch up with you later.

22:42.587 --> 22:44.628
Yeah, I'll see you guys later.

22:44.715 --> 22:47.467
- Baby, you're the best.
- She be givin' young one drama.

22:47.551 --> 22:50.634
- Seven years of the same shit.
- She makes it hard for sisters.

